It sounds like you are trying to build the Cathedral using wrong tools and instead of Cathedral you are getting pagan temple :)

1. technically, it is possible to override classpath/module dependencies imposed by parent pom by defining `system` scope, [something like](https://github.com/andreybpanfilov/so73747106/tree/system_scope_poc):

```
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.slf4j&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;slf4j-simple&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;2.0.1&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;scope&gt;system&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;systemPath&gt;${project.basedir}/../dummy.jar&lt;/systemPath&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

however, I wouldn&#39;t recommend to do that

2. another option is to take advantage of [classpathDependencyExcludes config option](https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/test-mojo.html#classpathDependencyExcludes) of surefire plugin, [something like](https://github.com/andreybpanfilov/so73747106/tree/classpathDependencyExcludes):

```
&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;configuration&gt;
        &lt;classpathDependencyExcludes&gt;org.slf4j:slf4j-simple&lt;/classpathDependencyExcludes&gt;
    &lt;/configuration&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```
3. If particular parent does not suit child&#39;s needs, child may adopt another parent :) There is no strict requirement that the aggregator pom must be the parent pom
4. the real problem is unlike [modern build tools](https://docs.gradle.org/current/userguide/java_library_plugin.html#sec:java_library_configurations_graph) maven does not distinguish `test compile` and `test runtime` scopes, however it is possible to [emulate such behaviour](https://github.com/andreybpanfilov/so73747106/tree/master)

```
&lt;properties&gt;
    &lt;surefire.runtime&gt;${project.build.directory}/surefire-runtime/slf4j-simple-2.0.1.jar&lt;/surefire.runtime&gt;
&lt;/properties&gt;

...

&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-dependency-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;executions&gt;
        &lt;execution&gt;
            &lt;id&gt;copy-surefire-runtime&lt;/id&gt;
            &lt;goals&gt;
                &lt;goal&gt;copy&lt;/goal&gt;
            &lt;/goals&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
                &lt;artifactItems&gt;
                    &lt;artifactItem&gt;
                        &lt;groupId&gt;org.slf4j&lt;/groupId&gt;
                        &lt;artifactId&gt;slf4j-simple&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                        &lt;version&gt;2.0.1&lt;/version&gt;
                        &lt;type&gt;jar&lt;/type&gt;
                        &lt;overWrite&gt;false&lt;/overWrite&gt;
                        &lt;outputDirectory&gt;${project.build.directory}/surefire-runtime/&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;
                    &lt;/artifactItem&gt;
                &lt;/artifactItems&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/execution&gt;
    &lt;/executions&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;configuration&gt;
        &lt;additionalClasspathElements&gt;${surefire.runtime}&lt;/additionalClasspathElements&gt;
    &lt;/configuration&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

yep, too many words there, but in my opinion that is only correct configuration for `test runtime` dependencies, m.b. it worth to submit a corresponding PR to surefire project - I believe that needs to write about 10 LoC to avoid `maven-dependency-plugin` configuration and able to configure `test runtime` in the following way:

```
&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;configuration&gt;
        &lt;additionalClasspathElements&gt;
            &lt;additionalClasspathElement&gt;org.slf4j:slf4j-api:2.0.1&lt;/additionalClasspathElement&gt;
        &lt;/additionalClasspathElements&gt;
    &lt;/configuration&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

